# Growth Ceiling

<%= partial(:cheat_column_start, :locals => { :text => 'Description:'}) %>
The maximum MRR that the current customer flows can support.
It's the point where the MRR from incoming customers matches the
MRR lost with the churned customers.
<%= partial 'cheat_column_end' %>

<%= partial(:cheat_column_start, :locals => { :text => 'Use:'}) %>
MRR growth will start to slow down when 70% - 80% of Growth Ceiling has been reached.
If Growth Ceiling is smaller than your current MRR, your business is shrinking towards the Growth Ceiling.
<br><br>Factors affecting Growth Ceiling are visualized in
<%= link_to 'MRR Growth View', 'https://www.firstofficer.io/mrr_growth' %>:<br>
<%= image_tag 'examples_mrr_growth_view.png' %>
<%= partial 'cheat_column_end' %>

<%= partial(:cheat_column_start, :locals => { :text => 'Target:'}) %>
In the growth phase, optimal growth ceiling is 2 times current MRR, or more.
Any growth ceiling that pleases the owners/investors is ok after the growth phase.
<%= partial 'cheat_column_end' %>

<%= partial(:cheat_column_start, :locals => { :text => 'To Improve it:'}) %>
